\ftnbj \fet\htmautsp\lnbrkrule
\formshade0\sectd\pgwsxn10479\pghsxn14642\marglsxn1272\margrsxn1272\margtsxn1532\margbsxn809\footery0\headery0\gutter0 \f5\fs18\fi0\ri0\li0\facingp\titlepg{\headerf}{\headerr}{\headerl}{\footerf}{\footerr}{\footerl}{\f5\fs18\fi0\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart codeChapter_5F272A}{\*\bkmkend codeChapter_5F272A}}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb600\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs24\qc\sb280{CHAPTER 272A}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\sb4\ri0\li0{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E2_2E2}{INTERSTATE AGREEMENT ON QUALIFICATION}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E2_2E2}\par}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\ri0\li0\sa0\par}{\pard\plain\keep\f5\fs18\qc\fi0\ri0\li0{ OF EDUCATIONAL PERSONNEL}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\fs2\qc\fi0\ri0\li0\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs17\fi0\sb280\ri0\li0\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{272A.1}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Interstate agreement.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The interstate agreement on qualification of educational personnel is hereby enacted into law and entered into with all jurisdictions legally joining therein, in the form substantially as follows:}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{1.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E4_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E4_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Article I \u8212\'3f Purpose, findings, and policy.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The states party to this agreement, desiring by common action to improve their respective school systems by utilizing the teacher or other professional educational person wherever educated, declare that it is the policy of each of them, on the basis of cooperation with one another, to take advantage of the preparation and experience of such persons wherever gained, thereby serving the best interest of society, of education, and of the teaching profession. It is the purpose of this agreement to provide for the development and execution of such programs of cooperation as will facilitate the movement of teachers and other professional educational personnel among the states party to it, and to authorize specific interstate educational personnel contracts to achieve that end.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The party states find that included in the large movement of population among all sections of the nation are many qualified educational personnel who move for family and other personal reasons but who are hindered in using their professional skill and experience in their new locations. Variations from state to state in requirements for qualifying educational personnel discourage such personnel from taking the steps necessary to qualify in other states. As a consequence, a significant number of professionally prepared and experienced educators is lost to our school systems. Facilitating the employment of qualified educational personnel, without reference to their states of origin, can increase the available educational resources. Participation in this agreement can increase the availability of educational personnel.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E5_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E5_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Article II \u8212\'3f Definitions.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{As used in this agreement and contracts made pursuant to it, unless the context clearly requires otherwise:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fAccept\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{, or any variant thereof, means to recognize and give effect to one or more determinations of another state relating to the qualifications of educational personnel in lieu of making or requiring a like determination that would otherwise be required by or pursuant to the laws of a receiving state.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fDesignated state official\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means the education official of a state selected by that state to negotiate and enter into, on behalf of that state, contracts pursuant to this agreement.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fEducational personnel\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means persons who must meet requirements pursuant to state law as a condition of employment in educational programs.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{d.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fOriginating state\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means a state, and the subdivision thereof, if any, whose determination that certain educational personnel are qualified to be employed for specific duties in schools is acceptable in accordance with the terms of a contract made pursuant to article III of this agreement.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{e.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fReceiving state\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means a state, and the subdivisions thereof, which accepts educational personnel in accordance with the terms of a contract made pursuant to article III of this agreement.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{f.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fState\u8221\'3f}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{ means a state, territory, or possession of the United States; the District of Columbia; or the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{3.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E6_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E6_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Article III \u8212\'3f Interstate educational personnel contracts.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The designated state official of a party state may make one or more contracts on behalf of that state with one or more other party states providing for the acceptance of educational personnel. Any such contract for the period of its duration shall be applicable to and binding on the states whose designated state officials enter into it, and the subdivisions of those states, with the same force and effect as if incorporated in this agreement. A designated state official may enter into a contract pursuant to this article only with states in which the official finds that there are programs of education, licensure standards or other acceptable qualifications that assure preparation or qualification of educational personnel on a basis sufficiently comparable, even though not identical to that prevailing in the official\u8217\'3fs state.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Any such contract shall provide for:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(1)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Its duration.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(2)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The criteria to be applied by an originating state in qualifying educational personnel for acceptance by a receiving state.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(3)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Such waivers, substitutions, and conditional acceptances as shall aid the practical effectuation of the contract without sacrifice of basic educational standards.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{(4)}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Any other necessary matters.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{No contract made pursuant to this agreement shall be for a term longer than five years but any such contract may be renewed for like or lesser periods.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{d.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Any contract dealing with acceptance of educational personnel on the basis of their having completed an educational program shall specify the earliest date or dates on which originating state approval of the program or programs involved can have occurred. No contract made pursuant to this agreement shall require acceptance by a receiving state of any persons qualified because of successful completion of a program prior to January 1, 1954.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{e.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The license or other acceptance of a person who has been accepted pursuant to the terms of a contract shall not be revoked or otherwise impaired because the contract has expired or been terminated. However, any license or other qualifying document may be revoked or suspended on any ground which would be sufficient for revocation or suspension of a license or other qualifying document initially granted or approved in the receiving state.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{f.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{A contract committee composed of the designated state officials of the contracting states or their representatives shall keep the contract under continuous review, study means of improving its administration, and report no less frequently than once a year to the heads of the appropriate education agencies of the contracting states.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{4.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E7_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E7_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Article IV \u8212\'3f Approved and accepted programs.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Nothing in this agreement shall be construed to repeal or otherwise modify any law or regulation of a party state relating to the approval of programs of educational preparation having effect solely on the qualification of educational personnel within that state.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{To the extent that contracts made pursuant to this agreement deal with the educational requirements for the proper qualification of educational personnel, acceptance of a program of educational preparation shall be in accordance with such procedures and requirements as may be provided in applicable contract.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{5.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E8_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E8_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Article V \u8212\'3f Interstate cooperation.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The party states agree that:}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{They will, so far as practicable, prefer the making of multilateral contracts pursuant to article III of this agreement.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{They will facilitate and strengthen cooperation in interstate certification and other elements of educational personnel qualification and for this purpose shall cooperate with agencies, organizations, and associations interested in certification and other elements of educational personnel qualification.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{6.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E9_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E9_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Article VI \u8212\'3f Agreement evaluation.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{The designated state officials of any party states may meet from time to time as a group to evaluate programs under the agreement, and to formulate recommendations for changes.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{7.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E1_30_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E1_30_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Article VII \u8212\'3f Other arrangements.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Nothing in this agreement shall be construed to prevent or inhibit other arrangements or practices of any party state or states to facilitate the interchange of educational personnel.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{8.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E11_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E11_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Article VIII \u8212\'3f Effect and withdrawal.}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{a.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{This agreement shall become effective when enacted into law by two states. Thereafter it shall become effective as to any state upon its enactment of this agreement.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{b.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Any party state may withdraw from this agreement by enacting a statute repealing the same, but no such withdrawal shall take effect until one year after the governor of the withdrawing state has given notice in writing of the withdrawal to the governors of all other party states.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{c.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{No withdrawal shall relieve the withdrawing state of any obligation imposed upon it by a contract to which it is a party. The duration of contracts and the methods and conditions of withdrawal therefrom shall be those specified in their terms.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{9.}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E4_2E12_2E1_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E4_2E12_2E1_2E2}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Article IX \u8212\'3f Construction and severability.}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{This agreement shall be liberally construed so as to effectuate the purposes thereof. The provisions of this agreement shall be severable and if any phrase, clause, sentence, or provision of this agreement is declared to be contrary to the constitution of any state or of the United States, or the application thereof to any government, agency, person, or circumstance is held invalid, the validity of the remainder of this agreement and the applicability thereof to any government, agency, person, or circumstance shall not be affected thereby. If this agreement shall be held contrary to the constitution of any state participating therein, the agreement shall remain in full force and effect as to the state affected as to all severable matters.}}}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7284.1}}}{]}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{90 Acts, ch 1249, \'a714}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{C93, \'a7272A.1}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2008 Acts, ch 1032, \'a7201}}}{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{; 2021 Acts, ch 76, \'a756}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\keep\keepn\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0\cbpat2{Referred to in }{{\f5\fs12\hyphpar0\qj{\'a7272A.2}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0\cbpat2\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{272A.2}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E5_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E5_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Designated state official.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{The designated state official for this state, within the meaning of }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 272A.1}}}{, article II, paragraph }{{\i\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\u8220\'3fb\u8221\'3f}}}{, of the interstate agreement on qualification of educational personnel, shall be the executive director of the board of educational examiners. The executive director shall enter into contracts pursuant to }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{section 272A.1}}}{, article III, of the agreement only with the approval of the specific text thereof by the board of educational examiners.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7284.2}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{85 Acts, ch 212, \'a721}}}{; }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{90 Acts, ch 1249, \'a715}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{C93, \'a7272A.2}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{2008 Acts, ch 1032, \'a7201}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\sb219\ri0\li0{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\chcbpat2}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{ }{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b0\fs24\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}\par}{\pard\plain\keepn\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{272A.3}}}{\*\bkmkstart stylerid1_2E6_2E2_2E2}{\*\bkmkend stylerid1_2E6_2E2_2E2}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{{\f5\b\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{Contracts on file.}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi0\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{\~\~}}}{True copies of all contracts made on behalf of this state pursuant to the interstate agreement on qualification of educational personnel shall be kept on file by the board of educational examiners and in the office of the secretary of state. The board of educational examiners shall publish all such contracts in convenient form. The board of educational examiners may adopt rules pursuant to }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{this chapter}}}{.}\par}{}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{[C75, 77, 79, }{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{81, \'a7284.3}}}{]}\par}{}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{90 Acts, ch 1249, \'a716}}}\par}{}{\pard\plain\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj\fi180\ri0\li0{{\f5\fs18\hyphpar0\qj{C93, \'a7272A.3}}}\par}}